 <br>
However, to the level 48 Warrior saying he wants a roll on the CoF: The point is that people 50 + don't have long to go before they out level these dragons, or they have put all exp into AA. at level 48 I don't think you CAN use AA. So either you are not serious about playing and only log on for Dragon raids, or you are a twink or someone and only played for dragon raids, or you are a loot whore who spends all their time in EC and thinks a CoF would get a nice price. Not be a bitch but there is NO reason to stop leveling at 48 in order to get a CoF. The people who are over 50 and have stopped are at least bettering their characters with AA which makes them much more powerful. Most of those people stop because they need the scale/book for their epic and a CoF would be a nice bonus since they have to do 100000 raids to get them usually. Also, a level 48 just isn't as useful for a tank as a level 50+ on these raids. You get new damage tables, etc post 50. So if you want to go to roll on the CoF, spend the time leveling up and earn it. It might be different if you were a class that is very needed, but generally warriors are jumping at the opportunity and there is not any trouble finding 10-15 or more post 50 tanks. <br>
<br>
Basically, these loot rules are worked out based on the reality that people stop leveling (at 52 when they either stop or don't go on the raids) to get a CoF. Or that someone post 50 may not be the right level long enough to go on another raid, where chances are if you are under 50 you will get in on at least one or two more. As an additonal thought, you cannot roll on the scale for your epic if you are under 50 (same reasons, not fair to the level 52 who has been waiting months if the level 48 gets the scale and is really to young to even DO the epic. Pay your dues then get the goods).  Naggy is fun to do for just a rush also. So go for the rush, or level up and go for the loot.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp. Sorry if I offended any one but that is the reality. It may not be fair to people under 50 but over 50 people are kinda really better to get it done fast and easy anyhow. Such are the facts of Norrath. <br>
<br>
<br>
 Good luck on the raid guys! It sucked that my last Naggy ever dropped practically the worse loot in history! But i wish you luck in a scale a book and 2 CoF on this one. :)<br>
